      "commit": {
        "parents": [
          {
            "commit": "3533c6a442a877d178d3c3c6fa078ec13aa973b1",
            "subject": "LU-6325 ptlrpc: make ptlrpcd threads cpt-aware"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Olaf Weber",
          "email": "olaf@sgi.com",
          "date": "2015-03-05 09:20:54.000000000",
          "tz": 60
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Olaf Weber",
          "email": "olaf@sgi.com",
          "date": "2015-03-05 12:00:37.000000000",
          "tz": 60
        },
        "subject": "LU-6325 ptlrpc: CPT-aware placement of ptlrpc_request_set",
        "message": "LU-6325 ptlrpc: CPT-aware placement of ptlrpc_request_set\n\nEnsure that the ptlrpc_request_set for a ptlrpcd thread is created on\nthe same CPT that the thread will work on. When threads are bound to\nspecific nodes and/or CPUs in a NUMA system, it pays to ensure that\nthe datastructures used by these threads are also on the same node.\n\nImplementation notes:\n\n* ptlrpc_prep_set_cpt(): New function, allocates a ptlrpc_request_set\n  on the specified CPT.\n\n* ptlrpc_prep_set(): Changed to forward to ptlrpc_prep_set_cpt(). It\n  specifies the use of the current CPT.\n\nThis change builds on\n  I3ac40ea56f9c792c3e7c36967e2e1f20105c566c\n\nTested-by: Stephen Champion <schamp@sgi.com>\nSigned-off-by: Olaf Weber <olaf@sgi.com>\nChange-Id: I38c5e40cdefc8c22ca697239004342c4c36a58ad\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
